## Project Signal System (PSS)

### 5-state machine

| State | Meaning | How it is reached |
|-------|---------|-------------------|
| ACTIVE | Process in progress | Organic (on mission creation) or `[[resume X]]` |
| PAUSED | Paused by explicit decision | `[[pause X]]` |
| WAITING | Waiting for external trigger or condition | `[[wait X]]` |
| COMPLETED | Finished (immutable) | `[[complete X]]` |
| EVOLUTION | New SIG derived from a COMPLETED one | Organic (new SIG with Ancestor) |

**Key distinction:** PAUSED = explicit decision. WAITING = waiting for external condition.

### Signal syntax

| Signal | Syntax | Type |
|--------|--------|------|
| Create | *(organic, on mission/process creation)* | Automatic |
| Pause | `[[pause X]]` | Explicit/contextual |
| Wait | `[[wait X]]` | Explicit/contextual |
| Resume | `[[resume X]]` | Explicit/contextual |
| Complete | `[[complete X]]` | Explicit/contextual |

### Propagation cascade

When any signal is emitted:
1. **SIGNAL_REGISTRY.md**: Create/update entry + signal history
2. **Mission target**: Update METADATA (State) + log entry
3. **MEMORY.md**: Update roadmap section if the mission is P1/P2

