## Mission Classification System

### Priorities (P1-P5)

| Level | Label | Meaning | Visibility in MEMORY.md |
|-------|-------|---------|-------------------------|
| P1 | CRITICAL | Active roadmap. Immediate integration | Roadmap + Catalog |
| P2 | HIGH | Important, plan soon. Impacts project goals | Roadmap + Catalog |
| P3 | MEDIUM | Valuable, wait for the right moment | Catalog only |
| P4 | LOW | Available when convenient | Catalog only |
| P5 | NOTE | Embryonic idea for the future | Catalog only |

### Mission types

| Type | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| ROOT | Trunk mission on the main development line |
| BRANCH | Child sub-mission of another mission (shares scope) |
| SATELLITE | Independent parallel project, not on the critical path |
| NOTE | Minimal record of a future idea without defined scope |

**Key principle:** Priority and type are orthogonal axes. A SATELLITE can be P1. A ROOT can be P3.

