## Project Handshake System (PHS)

### What is a handshake

A **handshake** is an immutable, chronological narrative checkpoint of the project's
state. One handshake is generated **before every commit that changes project content**.
Each handshake is self-contained: an LLM that reads only the latest handshake can
identify the project, understand its state, and continue work coherently.

The complete protocol lives in `specs/PHS-v1.0.md`. The summary below is the operational
contract every session must follow.

### Identifier and filename

| Element | Format | Example |
|---------|--------|---------|
| Identifier | `HS-NNN` (sequential, zero-padded, never reused) | `HS-007` |
| Filename | `handshakes/hs-NNN-YYYY-MM-DD-slug.md` | `handshakes/hs-007-2026-05-08-auth-phase-2.md` |

### Required sections in every handshake

1. Title and metadata block (HS-ID, project, date, slug, `Previous: HS-NNN`)
2. Executive Summary
3. System State
4. Advances Since Last Handshake
5. Files Created / Modified
6. Decisions Taken
7. Impact on Missions
8. Roadmap and Next Steps
9. Warnings and Risks
10. Context for External Agents

### Pre-commit protocol (strict ordering)

The following sequence is non-negotiable. The LLM agent performs steps 2-7 atomically
**before** the developer commits.

| Step | Action |
|------|--------|
| 1 | Complete all content changes (code, missions, memory, signals, etc.) |
| 2 | Read `HANDSHAKES.md`, determine next number N |
| 3 | Generate `handshakes/hs-N-YYYY-MM-DD-slug.md` from `templates/handshakes/_template.md` |
| 4 | Append entry to `HANDSHAKES.md` Quick Index |
| 5 | Update `HANDSHAKES.md` header (total, latest, last-updated) |
| 6 | Update `MEMORY.md` footer (`Handshakes: N (latest: HS-N)`) |
| 7 | Cross-reference HS-N in affected mission progress logs |
| 8 | Return control with: "handshake HS-N generated, ready to commit" |
| 9 | Developer commits |

If the commit happens before steps 5-6 complete, it captures stale counters and the
audit chain is broken. The agent MUST confirm step 8 explicitly so the developer knows
when it is safe to commit.

