## Session Protocol

### User commands and required actions

1. **"access memory"** or **"analyze memory"**
   - Read `MEMORY.md`
   - Confirm acquired context with summary: project state, active roadmap mission, total missions
   - Wait for instructions

2. **"analyze [name]"**
   - Find the mission associated with the name in MEMORY.md Catalog (Section 10)
   - Read the corresponding mission file
   - Confirm current state: phase, progress, priority, type
   - Wait for instructions

3. **"mission MIS-XXX"**
   - Read the corresponding file in `missions/`
   - Confirm current state and wait for instructions

4. **"[new mission: identifier]"**
   - Wait for exhaustive description from the user
   - Propose classification (Priority, Type, Parent, Dependencies)
   - Only after user validation, create the file
   - Register in MEMORY.md (Catalog always, Roadmap only if P1/P2)
   - Register signal in SIGNAL_REGISTRY.md (organic creation)

5. **"reclassify MIS-XXX [new priority/type]"**
   - Update METADATA in the mission file
   - If promoted to P1-P2: add to Roadmap
   - If demoted from P1-P2: remove from Roadmap, keep in Catalog

6. **"mission status"** or **"mission summary"**
   - Read MEMORY.md sections 9 and 10
   - Present executive summary: active roadmap + catalog statistics

7. **"roadmap"**
   - Read MEMORY.md section 9
   - Present only the active roadmap (P1-P2)

8. **"new handshake"** or **"generate handshake"**
   - Apply the PHS pre-commit protocol (see PHS section). In order:
     - Read `HANDSHAKES.md` to determine next HS number N
     - Create `handshakes/hs-N-YYYY-MM-DD-slug.md` from the handshake template, fill all 10 required sections
     - Append entry to `HANDSHAKES.md` Quick Index, update header (total, latest, last-updated)
     - Update `MEMORY.md` footer counter (`Handshakes: N (latest: HS-N)`)
     - Cross-reference HS-N in any mission progress logs touched in this work cycle
     - Return: "handshake HS-N generated, ready to commit"

9. **"handshakes"** or **"handshake history"**
   - Read `HANDSHAKES.md`
   - Present the Quick Index (chronological list of all handshakes)

10. **"handshake HS-NNN"**
    - Read `handshakes/hs-NNN-*.md` (resolve the slug from the filename)
    - Confirm content; wait for instructions

