## Update methodology

- **Mission files**: Update checks `[x]`, milestones, and progress log on each advance
- **MEMORY.md Roadmap (Section 9)**: Update when a P1/P2 mission changes state or phase
- **MEMORY.md Catalog (Section 10)**: Update when any mission is created or changes classification
- **MEMORY.md General (Sections 1-8)**: Update ONLY when a reached milestone affects global state
- **MEMORY.md footer**: Bump `Handshakes: N (latest: HS-N)` on every handshake generation
- **Signal Registry**: Update when signals are emitted (create, pause, wait, resume, complete)
- **HANDSHAKES.md**: Append a Quick Index entry on every handshake generation; update header counters
- **Handshake files**: Generated before every commit that changes project content. Immutable once written
- **SBS Beacons**: When updating any file, verify and update existing beacons if content has changed

