## Directory structure

```
{{PROJECT_ROOT}}/
├── COGNIDOC.md                    <- This file (protocol — auto-read by LLM)
├── MEMORY.md                      <- General project memory
├── SIGNAL_REGISTRY.md             <- Signal registry (process states)
├── HANDSHAKES.md                  <- Handshake index (chronological checkpoints)
├── missions/                      <- Individual mission memories
│   ├── mis-XXX-slug.md            <- Flat mission (no sub-missions)
│   └── mis-XXX-slug/              <- Mission promoted to folder (with sub-missions)
│       ├── mis-XXX-slug.md        <- Main mission file
│       └── mis-YYY-sub.md         <- Sub-mission (BRANCH)
└── handshakes/                    <- Immutable handshake files
    └── hs-NNN-YYYY-MM-DD-slug.md  <- One per commit that changes project content
```

### File-to-folder promotion

- Every new mission starts as a flat file: `mis-XXX-slug.md`
- When a mission receives its first BRANCH sub-mission:
  1. Create folder `mis-XXX-slug/`
  2. Move the file inside: `mis-XXX-slug/mis-XXX-slug.md`
  3. Create the sub-mission inside: `mis-XXX-slug/mis-YYY-sub.md`
- Maximum nesting: 3 levels
- IDs are always global sequential (MIS-001, MIS-002...), never nested

