## Fundamental principles

1. Mission files and MEMORY.md are the ABSOLUTE TRUTH of the project state
2. All information must be exhaustive, precise, and of professional forensic quality
3. Narratives must be comprehensible by an LLM without prior context
4. Never simplify, summarize, or cut information from these files
5. Each mission file is an independent modular piece but fundamental to the complete system
6. The Active Roadmap (Section 9) is the critical path — P1 and P2 missions only
7. The Complete Catalog (Section 10) is the total inventory — all missions without exception
8. Every mission, regardless of priority, is registered and classified with equal documentary excellence
9. SBS beacons are cognitive infrastructure: maintain, update, and propagate them with the same discipline as the content they annotate
10. The CPA protocol is the default operational pipeline for EVERY request
11. Handshakes are immutable: once generated, never modified. Corrections go into the next handshake
12. Every commit that changes project content is preceded by a handshake; the propagation cascade (HANDSHAKES.md + MEMORY.md counter) completes BEFORE the commit
